"gloss":"similar, like, matching"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"equal"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Akkadian naṣārum (𒈾𒍝𒊒, “to watch over, protect”), Aramaic נְטַר (nəṭar, “to watch, guard”), Classical Syriac ܢܛܲܪ (nəṭar, “to watch”) and Hebrew נָצַר (nɔṣár, “to keep, maintain”)."},"ipa":["/na.ðˤa.ra/","/naðˤ.ðˤa.ra/","/na.ðˤar/","/niðˤr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40045","headword_ar":"نَظَرٌ","root":"nZr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1. [Used as a subst., as well as when used as an inf. n.,] it has no pl. (Sb, in TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fikorN","text_ar":"فِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabonaAhumo binaZar","text_ar":"ضَرَبْنَاهُمْ بِنَظَر"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino naZari","text_ar":"مِنْ نَظَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We saw them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonanaA naZarN","text_ar":"بَيْنَنَا نَظَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between us is the extent of a look in respect of nearness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N naZarN","text_ar":"حَىٌّ نَظَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilaAlN wanaZarN","text_ar":"جِلَالٌ وَنَظَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N HilaAlN wariyaA='N wanaZarN","text_ar":"حَىٌّ حِلَالٌ وَرِيَا=ءٌ وَنَظَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tribe went together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the several portions see one another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wafiyhi naZarN","text_ar":"وَفِيهِ نَظَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But it requires consideration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of its want of clearness, or perspicuity: (Msb:) [a phrase used to imply doubt, and also to insinuate politely that the words to which it relates are false, or wrong:] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi taA^am~ulN","text_ar":"فِيهِ تَاَمُّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SfH","text_ar":"صفح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa bixayori Aln~aZaryoni","text_ar":"هُوَ بِخَيْرِ النَّظَريْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said in a trad., of one who has purchased a ewe or she-goat that has been kept from being milked for some days; meaning, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has the option of adopting the better of the two things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"he may either retain it or return it. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}